{ In the left side of the screen you have the option to select any line you want to train, but just remember that your dear author recommends starting in chronological order.

Behind the board you will always see two buttons that can start a drill mode:
1.drill with arrows (based on arrows + piece highlight)
-your best friend when encountering new variations
2.drill without arrows (no help of any kind, only if you want it)
-this mode is supposed to really cement the ideas in your brain and it's the final test before moving to a new variation

To enhance the learning experience, I suggest the following workflow for every new variation that you are trying to learn:
-at first we drill 'with arrows' until no mistakes are made
-then we drill using the 'without' button until no mistakes are made
-once you are comfortable drilling the line without help, then it's time to select 'next variation' and repeat the process }
 *


