[UTCTime "19:58:56"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/RoyalFlushDraw"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/8tMJrAWn/6uPdc6tm"]

{ The repertoire will be split into 5 thematic structures.

Black doesn't fight for the center:
1.English Attack: triggered by Black not playing ...d5
(1.d4 Nf6 2.Nc3 g6 3.e4 d6 4.f3 Bg7 5.Be3)

Black plays light squared bishop INSIDE the pawn chain:
2.Colosseum structure: resulting from ...Bb4 pin
(1.d4 d5 2.Nc3 Nf6 3.Bf4 e6 4.e3 Bb4 5.Bd3 Bxc3+ 6.bxc3)
3.Boa Snake structure: resulting from ...Bd6 move
(1.d4 d5 2.Nc3 Nf6 3.Bf4 e6 4.e3 Bd6 5.Bd3 Bxf4 6.exf4)
4.Pandora's box: resulting from ...Be7 move
(1.d4 d5 2.Nc3 Nf6 3.Bf4 e6 4.e3 Be7 5.Bd3 c6 6.Nf3 0-0 7.0-0 Nbd7 8.e4)

Black plays light squared bishop OUTSIDE the pawn chain
5.Pawn storm structure: triggered by ...Bf5/Bg4 move
(1.d4 d5 2.Nc3 Nf6 3.Bf4 Bf5 4.f3)

To get your foot in the door, I've prepared the most important seven variations. These are gonna be enough to start playing 1.d4 in your games (in case you never did before).

The starter-pack ends with the 'BIG QUIZ' which is just a compilation of all the 7 trainables. If you can solve that one without arrows, congrats! You have mastered the starter-pack.

This is pretty much all you need to know about how the platform works, the rest will be easy to figure out along the way...so I invite you to press 'next chapter' and dive into the quiz. }
 *


